[As mentioned previously, this website is constantly updated as new information comes in, so it is likely that when you read this post, the numbers will not match the linked numbers because they will have been updated since the post was prepared.

According to the data on the Johns Hopkins website, there are now a total of 17 819 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 91 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 2816 cases reported in the past 24 hours, with Italy accounting for 769 of newly reported cases, Iran for 591 of the newly reported cases, and South Korea for 518 of newly reported cases. Other countries experiencing increases of more than 10 cases include Germany, 283 new cases; France, 138; USA, 76; Spain, 60; Sweden, 59; Netherlands, 44; Norway, 35; UK, 31; Switzerland, 29; Japan, 29; Greece, 22; and Austria, 14. A global total of 3383 deaths have been reported, 341 outside mainland China.

Of note, reading the media reports on Costa Rica, the government reported the 1st suspected case but infection with the SARS-CoV-2 has not been confirmed at the time of preparation of this report.

For the 9th consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. - Mod.MPP]

