[2] China: China National Health Commission 5 Mar 2020
Date: Fri 6 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans. edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/b59dbcc84ed1498292714975039dcdc9.shtml


At 04:00 on [5 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 143 new confirmed cases, 30 new deaths (29 in Hubei, and 1 in Hainan), and new suspected cases. 102 cases.

On the same day, 1681 new cases recovered and were discharged, and 5457 close contacts were lifted from medical observation. The number of severe cases decreased by 215.

As of 24:00 on [5 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 23 784 confirmed cases (among which, 5737 were severe cases), 53 726 had recovered and been discharged, and 3042 had died. A total of 80 552 confirmed cases have been reported, and there are 482 suspected cases. A total of 670 854 close contacts had been traced, and 29 896 close contacts were still under medical observation.

There were 126 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (126 in Wuhan), 1487 newly recovered cases (1038 in Wuhan), 29 new deaths (23 in Wuhan), and 22 695 confirmed cases (20 115 in Wuhan). Among them, 5588 cases were severe cases (5208 cases in Wuhan). A total of 41 966 discharged patients were cured (27 354 in Wuhan), a total of 2931 deaths (2328 in Wuhan), and a total of 67 592 confirmed cases (49 797 in Wuhan). There were 43 new suspected cases (42 in Wuhan) and 285 suspected cases (232 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [5 Mar 2020], 16 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported (11 in Gansu, 4 in Beijing, and 1 in Shanghai). As of 24:00 on [5 Mar 2020], a total of 36 imported confirmed cases were reported overseas.

A total of 158 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 104 cases in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (46 cases discharged, 2 deaths), 10 cases in the Macao Special Administrative Region (9 cases discharged), and 44 cases in Taiwan (12 cases discharged, 1 case died).

