[According to the report above, a total of 80 552 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from China, representing an increase of 143 cases in the past 24 hours, of which 126 (88%) were in Hubei province. In addition, 30 deaths were reported, of which 29 (97%) were reported by Hubei province. No new cases were reported from Hong Kong.

Of note is the mention of 16 newly imported cases (11 in Gansu, 4 in Beijing, and 1 in Shanghai), bringing the total number of imported cases to 36. It would be of interest to know where the importations were from.

