[Note that the reporting interval is now midnight to midnight, presenting the full calendar day. In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 518 cases and 7 deaths.

Daegu province and Gyeongbuk provinces continue to have reported the highest number of cases, 4693 and 984, respectively. Daegu is completely surrounded by Gyeongbuk province in the central eastern part of South Korea. Daegu has been the epicenter of this ongoing outbreak. While several provinces are at or approaching 100 cases (Gyeonggi: 120, Seoul 105, Busan 95, Chungnam 90), the rate of growth in numbers of daily new cases appears to be at a much slower pace than that seen in Daegu and Gyeongbuk.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7056224,195. - Mod.MPP]

