B. Italy: 3858 cases, 148 deaths
Date: Thu 5 Mar 2020
Source: Italian Government Health Ministry [in Italian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/news/p3_2_1_1_1.jsp?lingua=italiano&menu=notizie&p=dalministero&id=4157


Cases in Italy as of 6:00 pm 5 Mar 2020
---------------------------------------
Regarding health monitoring related to the spread of the new coronavirus [SARS-CoV-2] in national territories, a total of 3858 people have been infected to date, and 3296 people are currently positive for the virus. 414 people have recovered. There are 1790 patients hospitalized with symptoms, 351 are in intensive care, and 1165 are in home isolation.

There have been 148 reported deaths, but this number can be confirmed only after the Istituto Superiore di Sanità has established the actual cause of death.

The number of people infected in the individual regions is as follows:
- Lombardy 2251
