[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is now 3858, including 148 deaths, up from 2706 cases and 107 deaths reported on 4 Mar 2020. Newly mentioned provinces and autonomous entities reporting confirmed cases include Aosta Valley. Cases continue to be concentrated in Lombardy (2251), the epicenter of the outbreak, Emilia-Romagna (698), and Venice (407), all in the northern part of the county. Italy is a major tourist point and Lombardy is a major commercial hub. In addition, Italians are highly mobile and travel throughout Europe and the Americas. See section [4] below for imported cases from Italy to other countries in Europe and in other regions, a sign of this mobility.

A map of Italy showing regions can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/italy/regions.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7056224,75. - Mod.MPP]

