[In the past 24 hours, the number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran has grown from 2922 to 3513, an increase of 591 newly confirmed cases. The number of deaths has also increased from 92 to 107, an increase of 15 deaths.

Qom, the apparent epicenter of this outbreak, is located to the south west of Tehran in central Iran. Other media reports have mentioned that Tehran has become a major focus of cases. According to the above report, all but 1 of the 31 provinces have reported cases.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7056224,128. - Mod.MPP]

