[Among the 5 new countries reporting confirmed cases of SARS-CoV-2 infection, transmission in 3 occurred in Italy, (1 in Morocco or Italy), 1 in either the USA or India, and 1 is unspecified.

The unspecified transmission area involves hotel employees in Bethlehem (investigated after Greek tourists returned to Greece infected. Remembering the incident of the South Korean tourists from the evangelical sect that went to Israel and the West Bank for religious tourism and upon return to South Korea were identified as COVID-19 cases, one can't help but wonder if they had stayed in a hotel in Bethlehem and may have started the transmission chain there. This same group was the beginning of the major outbreak ongoing in South Korea. More information on the investigation in Bethlehem would be greatly appreciated. - Mod.MPP]

