A. France ex Egypt
Date: Thu 5 Mar 2020 20:39 CET+01:00
Source: The Local [abridged, edited]
https://www.thelocal.fr/20200305/latest-number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-france-rises-to-130


Authorities also confirmed that cases have now been reported in all regions of mainland France -- although the highest numbers remain concentrated in 4 'cluster zones' -- Mulhouse in the Haut-Rhin department in eastern France, Oise in the north east (55 cases), Morbihan (20 cases) in Brittany, and Haute-Savoie in the Alps (44 cases).

A 5th cluster was a tour group that had travelled to Egypt, with 13 people testing positive for the infection.

