B. Greece ex West Bank/Egypt/Israel
Date: Thu 5 Mar 2020 05:31 PM
Source: i24News, Agence France Presses (AFP) report [edited]
https://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/1583413467-greece-group-of-21-tourists-returning-from-israel-egypt-infected-with-virus


Greek health officials on Thursday [5 Mar 2020] reported 21 new coronavirus infections [COVID-19] among a group that had recently traveled to Israel and Egypt by bus, raising the country's total to 31. "It was a closed group of people who were on a bus for several days," Sotiris Tsiodras of the national public health organization (EODY) told a news conference, adding that they had returned to Greece on [27 Feb 2020]. The group had been on a Holy Land trip to Israel and Egypt, EODY said.

Two among the group -- an elderly man and his wife -- had already tested positive as Greece's 9th and 10th cases, respectively. The 66 year old man has acute pneumonia and is in a stable condition, EODY said. Another 21 among the group were confirmed on Thursday [5 Mar 2020], Tsiodras said. He added that most of the patients are in good health and are being monitored at home.

Officials last night [4 Mar 2020] announced a 2-day school shutdown and a cancellation of public events in the areas in western Greece where the group had come from. The 2-day shutdown included "a suspension of all mass gatherings" at theaters, cinemas, museums, and sports events in the Peloponnese regions of Achaia and Elis and the island of Zakynthos through to Friday [6 Mar 2020].

Ancient Olympia, where the flame for the Tokyo 2020 Olympics is scheduled to be lit on [12 Mar 2020], is in Elis. The Greek Olympic Committee this week said it was limiting festivities and cancelling all event dinners and galas. The situation will be re-evaluated regularly, it added. The coronavirus outbreak has infected more than 95 000 people worldwide and killed over 3200.

--
