[I have a déjà vu sense, remembering the saga of the Diamond Princess. Presumably, the intention is to begin with testing the "suspected" cases, (a headline said, "only 110 to be tested" and close contacts. Presumably, should there be confirmed cases, the net will be widened to test the entire passengers and crew. A delay in doing so was a major stumbling block in the management of the Diamond Princess cases. Clearly, once cases are identified, there will probably be more people infected with the SARS-CoV-2 during the stay onboard the boat. We await further information. - Mod.MPP]

