[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 outside China continues to grow and now totals 84. This includes 9 countries from the Western Pacific region, 41 countries (including 1 territory) from the European region, 5 countries from the Southeast Asia region, 16 countries (including 1 territory) from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 10 countries (including 2 territories) from the Americas region, and 3 countries from the African region. 31 countries are listed as having local transmission within their countries, with Belgium, Belarus and Portugal newly reporting local transmission. Local transmission was also noted on the cruise ship that was quarantined in Japan (the Diamond Princess).

The total number of cases reported from outside of China is now 14 768 including 267 deaths.

A somewhat repetitive but necessary reminder: it is clear that the number of reported confirmed cases differs from different reporting websites and is somewhat a function of time of day the website is updated. For example, I note the time I've accessed the Johns Hopkins website, but by the time the post is actually finished with the editing process, those numbers have at times significantly changed. Case counting is clearly a moving target, and, depending upon when the website updates, the numbers may be different. - Mod.MPP]
